WEBVTT

00:01.126 --> 00:02.711
Previously on "Manifest"...

00:02.711 --> 00:04.963
He's coming.
He's almost here.

00:04.963 --> 00:06.715
[ Grunts ]

00:06.715 --> 00:08.175
Maybe you're supposed
to come back with me.

00:08.175 --> 00:10.093
Go back where?
Back to the world?

00:10.093 --> 00:12.137
I'm not sure the world
wants me back.

00:12.137 --> 00:13.597
We need to figure out
what Zeke's return

00:13.597 --> 00:15.182
means for
the bigger picture.

00:15.182 --> 00:16.683
Ben just moved out.
The couch is free,

00:16.683 --> 00:18.435
so you can crash here
for a bit.

00:18.435 --> 00:20.687
I love you.
It's always been you.

00:22.773 --> 00:25.025
I can't get over what we did.
It's not right.

00:25.025 --> 00:26.485
We're supposed
to be together, Mick.

00:26.485 --> 00:28.946
Supposed to be or not,
we're -- we're not together.

00:28.946 --> 00:30.322
You're with Lourdes.

00:30.322 --> 00:31.657
Jared, what's going on?

00:31.657 --> 00:33.617
I just need some time.

00:33.617 --> 00:34.660
Where is she?

00:34.660 --> 00:36.119
She's gone, Mick.

00:36.119 --> 00:37.454
Why did you tell her?

00:37.454 --> 00:39.081
I didn't have to.
She already knew.

00:39.081 --> 00:40.582
I want you
to make him better.

00:40.582 --> 00:42.417
There is nothing
I can do to help --

00:44.086 --> 00:45.462
Alice.

00:46.463 --> 00:48.465
Zeke: I saw a wolf.
Or at least I imagined one.

00:48.465 --> 00:50.050
You, too?

00:50.050 --> 00:51.593
Ben: Aunt Michaela?

00:51.593 --> 00:53.428
I need one of you down
on the waterfront.

00:53.428 --> 00:55.389
Recovery of the getaway vehicle
from that armored-car heist

00:55.389 --> 00:56.765
that went into
the East River.

00:56.765 --> 00:58.016
It's going on
four days now.

00:58.016 --> 00:59.601
Michaela: The body's
still inside.

01:00.936 --> 01:02.813
[ Gasps ]
[ Screams ]

01:04.940 --> 01:14.741
♪♪

01:14.741 --> 01:24.584
♪♪

01:24.584 --> 01:34.386
♪♪

01:34.386 --> 01:44.021
♪♪

01:44.021 --> 01:46.064
[ Electricity crackles ]
[ Groans ]

01:46.064 --> 01:47.858
[ People shouting ]

01:47.858 --> 01:49.985
[ Electricity crackles ]

01:49.985 --> 01:51.278
[ Groans ]

01:51.278 --> 01:55.157
♪♪

01:55.157 --> 01:57.617
Man: Stay down!
Stay down! Stay down!

01:57.617 --> 02:05.709
♪♪

02:05.709 --> 02:13.800
♪♪

02:13.800 --> 02:15.052
[ Engine starts ]

02:15.052 --> 02:17.888
[ Tires squeal ]

02:17.888 --> 02:25.520
♪♪

02:25.520 --> 02:29.566
[ Sirens wailing ]

02:31.526 --> 02:33.028
Hey.
Where are you taking him?

02:33.028 --> 02:34.404
Mercy.
I've got no room.

02:34.404 --> 02:35.906
We got a uni riding
with him already.

02:35.906 --> 02:37.449
I can follow behind.
But he can't go to Mercy.

02:37.449 --> 02:38.909
He's got to go
to Ed Koch.
What?

02:38.909 --> 02:40.911
Nah.
Mercy's closer.
No, no, trust me.

02:40.911 --> 02:43.038
Koch has hyperbaric
oxygen chambers.

02:43.038 --> 02:45.248
For how long he's been
underwater, he's gonna need one.

02:48.210 --> 02:49.961
We're gonna reroute to Koch.
Come on. Let's go.

02:49.961 --> 02:52.964
♪♪

02:52.964 --> 02:54.966
[ Ambulance doors close,
engine starts ]

02:54.966 --> 02:57.677
♪♪

02:57.677 --> 03:00.680
[ Engines roaring ]

03:00.680 --> 03:04.684
♪♪

03:04.684 --> 03:07.062
The getaway car disappeared
three days ago.

03:07.062 --> 03:08.897
Authorities are speculating
that sediment

03:08.897 --> 03:11.900
at the river bottom
obscured its location.

03:11.900 --> 03:14.111
Now, incredibly,
the driver's been pulled

03:14.111 --> 03:16.029
from the vehicle, alive.

03:16.029 --> 03:19.157
This is Michelle Park...
A van disappears
in a river for days,

03:19.157 --> 03:22.119
then suddenly reappears,
and the driver's okay?

03:22.119 --> 03:23.537
I know.

03:23.537 --> 03:24.955
Do you think...?

03:24.955 --> 03:27.582
Why not?
Zeke came back.

03:27.582 --> 03:29.584
I mean, the question is,
why no one

03:29.584 --> 03:31.920
for an entire six weeks
since the plane returned --

03:31.920 --> 03:33.630
and then two
in one week?

03:33.630 --> 03:36.466
Nobody knows about me.
Who's to say there aren't more?

03:36.466 --> 03:38.927
[ Cellphone ringing, buzzing ]

03:38.927 --> 03:41.054
It's Michaela.

03:41.054 --> 03:42.431
Did you get
a good look at him?

03:42.431 --> 03:43.974
I just sent you a picture.

03:43.974 --> 03:46.268
Ben, the guy was underwater
for over 80 hours.

03:46.268 --> 03:48.895
He should be a bloated corpse
right now. He should be dead.

03:48.895 --> 03:51.940
Maybe he wasn't underwater
the whole time.

03:51.940 --> 03:55.152
Maybe it's some kind of scam
we're just not seeing yet.

03:55.152 --> 03:56.611
No, you wouldn't be
saying that

03:56.611 --> 03:58.029
if you saw the way
he just jumped out of his skin.

03:58.029 --> 03:58.947
He jumped at me.

03:58.947 --> 04:01.199
Which is exactly
what Cal drew. The wolf.

04:03.326 --> 04:05.537
You think this guy's
one of us?

04:05.537 --> 04:08.915
Meet me at Koch
in 20 minutes.

04:08.915 --> 04:11.543
Mick's headed to this hospital
with this guys. I've --

04:11.543 --> 04:13.753
Yeah, yeah. Go.
The kids are asleep.
I want answers, too.

04:13.753 --> 04:15.255
So do I.

04:15.255 --> 04:16.840
This guy
wasn't on the plane?

04:16.840 --> 04:19.384
If he's like me,
I'm going with you.

04:21.720 --> 04:24.222
EMT: 30-something male
recovered from the East River.

04:24.222 --> 04:25.891
Breathing is shallow.
He's barely conscious.

04:25.891 --> 04:27.517
We started him on O2
and saline.

04:27.517 --> 04:29.853
Heart rate is steady,
BP 135 over 70.

04:29.853 --> 04:30.896
You've got to wait out here,
Detective.

04:30.896 --> 04:33.231
We'll find you later.

04:33.231 --> 04:34.733
Michaela!

04:34.733 --> 04:36.485
Hey. What's going on?

04:36.485 --> 04:37.944
How's this guy
still alive?

04:39.488 --> 04:41.364
I don't know.

04:41.364 --> 04:43.033
What is it?

04:43.033 --> 04:46.077
Cal knew he'd be alive.
Or it seems like it at least.

04:46.077 --> 04:47.621
Listen, Jared --
Wait. Whoa, whoa.

04:47.621 --> 04:50.373
You're saying he came back,
like the plane?

04:50.373 --> 04:51.708
Like you and Ben?

04:51.708 --> 04:54.544
Yeah, it's possible.

04:54.544 --> 04:57.339
He wouldn't be the first.
Somebody else came back.

04:57.339 --> 04:59.382
What?

04:59.382 --> 05:00.967
His name is Zeke.

05:00.967 --> 05:02.010
He walked out
of a cave upstate --

05:02.010 --> 05:05.388
one year
after he disappeared.

05:05.388 --> 05:08.850
That's why you were up there?
Why didn't you tell me?

05:10.727 --> 05:12.938
I should have, but I'm still
processing a lot of this.

05:12.938 --> 05:14.856
And there's a lot going on
between you and me. I-I just --

05:14.856 --> 05:16.233
You don't shut me out, either,
Mick.

05:16.233 --> 05:17.400
Not with something
as big as this.

05:17.400 --> 05:18.443
Somebody just came back,
though.

05:18.443 --> 05:19.945
Something is happening
right now.

05:19.945 --> 05:21.571
Detectives.

05:21.571 --> 05:24.282
Detectives, I could really use
your help over here.

05:24.282 --> 05:25.867
I'll take care of it.

05:25.867 --> 05:30.455
[ Indistinct shouting ]

05:30.455 --> 05:31.706
Hey.

05:31.706 --> 05:34.543
Ambulance driver fell
for the oxygen-chamber excuse?

05:34.543 --> 05:36.753
Yeah.
Good call by you.

05:36.753 --> 05:38.547
Okay, let's see how close
we can get to him.

05:38.547 --> 05:40.757
Hey. This doesn't
look very good.

05:40.757 --> 05:42.676
It could've been
a lot worse.

05:42.676 --> 05:44.511
[ Indistinct shouting ]

05:44.511 --> 05:46.638
Excuse me. Let them through,
they're with me.

05:48.682 --> 05:51.184
So, what do we know?
Has he said anything?
Done anything?

05:51.184 --> 05:54.521
He's in the E.R. right now.
Mick and Saanvi are on it.

05:54.521 --> 05:55.897
I don't think we've met.

05:55.897 --> 05:57.357
Uh, uh, this is...

05:57.357 --> 05:59.609
Zeke.
From the cave.

05:59.609 --> 06:01.486
Word gets around.

06:01.486 --> 06:02.946
I got to take care
of that out there.

06:02.946 --> 06:04.281
So why don't you guys
wait in this room?

06:04.281 --> 06:06.074
Yeah. Sure.

06:06.074 --> 06:08.702
You know what?
Do me a favor.

06:08.702 --> 06:10.579
Don't leave before we get
a chance to talk.

06:13.039 --> 06:14.416
What was that about?

06:14.416 --> 06:15.792
Does he got some kind
of problem with me?

06:15.792 --> 06:17.335
Jared and Michaela
were a couple.

06:17.335 --> 06:19.879
He proposed.
Then the plane disappeared.

06:19.879 --> 06:24.593
Since we've been back,
it's been...complicated.

06:26.011 --> 06:27.429
[ Cellphone chimes ]

06:27.429 --> 06:29.264
I just got
the incident report.

06:29.264 --> 06:31.933
It says that the car went into
the water Wednesday 11:06 a.m.

06:31.933 --> 06:33.560
3 1/2 days ago.

06:33.560 --> 06:36.187
And he got out tonight
at what time?

06:36.187 --> 06:39.608
9:14 p.m.

06:39.608 --> 06:43.612
Michaela, that's 82 hours
and 8 minutes.

06:43.612 --> 06:46.031
828.

06:46.031 --> 06:47.741
[ Clatters ]
[ Gasps ]

06:47.741 --> 06:48.825
...to help --

06:48.825 --> 06:51.703
[ Breathing heavily ]

06:51.703 --> 06:53.788
Hey. You okay?

06:53.788 --> 06:55.373
I'm fine. I'm fine.

06:55.373 --> 06:58.251
I'm just --
I'm overwhelmed I think.

06:58.251 --> 07:00.754
Three days submerged and no sign
of fluid in his lungs?

07:00.754 --> 07:03.423
No respiratory impairment,
no cardiac arrest, no hypoxia.

07:03.423 --> 07:04.883
It's like he was never
underwater.

07:04.883 --> 07:06.551
Get them away!
Get them away!

07:06.551 --> 07:08.303
-Calm down!
-No! No! No! No!

07:08.303 --> 07:09.554
Get them away from there!

07:09.554 --> 07:11.431
They're gonna die!
I can see it!

07:11.431 --> 07:12.891
Does that look
familiar to you?

07:12.891 --> 07:14.476
It's a calling.

07:14.476 --> 07:16.603
Griffin, Griffin,
what are you seeing right now?

07:16.603 --> 07:19.731
An explosion!
There's a fire! There's fire!

07:19.731 --> 07:21.733
I see smoke!
There's planes!

07:21.733 --> 07:23.818
An explosion? Can you tell me
exactly where it is?

07:23.818 --> 07:25.570
He's delusional.
No, he's not.

07:25.570 --> 07:26.863
Can you step out of my E.R.,
please?

07:26.863 --> 07:28.323
People are dying!

07:28.323 --> 07:30.116
There's children!
People are screaming!

07:30.116 --> 07:32.452
Heart rate's spiking.
Push 10 milligrams of midazolam.

07:32.452 --> 07:33.995
No, no, no! W-Wait! Wait!
Do not sedate him!

07:33.995 --> 07:35.664
Hey!
You two, out of here!

07:35.664 --> 07:37.082
No!
Griffin, what are you seeing?
Gotta go.

07:37.082 --> 07:38.583
Griffin,
where is this happening?
Come on.

07:38.583 --> 07:40.710
Griffin! Griffin!
Out, out.

07:40.710 --> 07:47.425
♪♪

07:50.845 --> 07:53.223
And you're sure
it was a calling?

07:53.223 --> 07:55.141
Yes, I'm sure.
He was having a vision, Ben.

07:55.141 --> 07:57.352
It was -- It was an explosion
of some kind.

07:57.352 --> 07:59.229
He kept saying,
"People are dying."

07:59.229 --> 08:00.730
Which means will be.
And soon.

08:00.730 --> 08:02.899
The callings have always
been urgent.

08:02.899 --> 08:04.526
How long
will he be out for?

08:04.526 --> 08:06.319
A couple of hours
at least.

08:06.319 --> 08:07.779
Hopefully
we're not too late.

08:07.779 --> 08:09.698
What do we know
about this guy?

08:11.324 --> 08:12.701
His name
is James Griffin.

08:12.701 --> 08:15.078
He's known for aggravated
assault, armed robbery,

08:15.078 --> 08:16.871
and, now,
a double homicide.

08:16.871 --> 08:18.707
Why does this guy
get to come back?

08:18.707 --> 08:19.791
Yeah, I don't understand.

08:19.791 --> 08:21.126
I thought the callings
were all about a bigger purpose,

08:21.126 --> 08:23.211
but how does this guy
fit into that?

08:23.211 --> 08:23.920
And why now?

08:23.920 --> 08:26.673
Why two non-passengers
returning back-to-back?

08:26.673 --> 08:28.883
Really? You're gonna lump me and
Natural Born Killer in together?

08:28.883 --> 08:30.218
No, no. I'm just saying,
there has to be

08:30.218 --> 08:32.679
a logic to his return,
a reason.

08:32.679 --> 08:34.347
Even if it's not
for doing good.

08:34.347 --> 08:36.558
Whatever it is, Michaela
is somehow in the middle of it.

08:36.558 --> 08:39.185
Cal's calling
led you to me.

08:39.185 --> 08:43.022
His next calling
led you to Griffin.

08:43.022 --> 08:44.858
Assuming Griffin's
the wolf...

08:44.858 --> 08:46.568
He's got to be.

08:46.568 --> 08:48.987
Michaela: He jumped out
of the van at me, and...

08:48.987 --> 08:49.738
I mean, it tracks.

08:49.738 --> 08:52.282
The calling wanted me
to help you understand it.

08:52.282 --> 08:54.826
Maybe I'm supposed
to help Griffin, too.

08:54.826 --> 08:57.996
Even though
he's a terrible person?

08:57.996 --> 09:00.039
A terrible person
with information

09:00.039 --> 09:01.583
that could avert
a disaster.

09:01.583 --> 09:04.169
Fine.
I need to test Griffin's blood.

09:04.169 --> 09:06.254
See if he has the same marker
as Zeke.

09:06.254 --> 09:10.258
♪♪

09:10.258 --> 09:11.968
Hey, you should keep
an eye on her.

09:11.968 --> 09:14.429
She went through massive trauma.
She's not doing okay.

09:14.429 --> 09:19.100
♪♪

09:19.100 --> 09:22.020
[ Police radio chatter ]

09:22.020 --> 09:25.273
Hey. Griffin's under guard.
I put a couple guys on him.

09:25.273 --> 09:27.442
I want to talk to him
as soon as he's conscious.

09:27.442 --> 09:30.361
Yeah, well,
we've got some time.

09:30.361 --> 09:32.238
Why don't you and I
go for breakfast?

09:34.532 --> 09:37.494
Um...
Sorry to stick my nose in,
but you gotta be wiped.

09:37.494 --> 09:39.788
Why don't you find
a couch while you wait?

09:39.788 --> 09:41.748
Name's Zeke, right?

09:41.748 --> 09:43.291
Yeah.
Mm.

09:43.291 --> 09:44.959
Zeke what?
Jared.

09:44.959 --> 09:48.004
So you were upstate
when you returned?

09:48.004 --> 09:50.757
Is that right?
Is that where you're from?

09:50.757 --> 09:52.133
Can we not do this
right now?

09:52.133 --> 09:54.135
Just want some answers.
That's all.

09:54.135 --> 09:55.637
Y-You got a murderer
in the next room,

09:55.637 --> 09:58.431
maybe you ought
to be thinking about that.

09:58.431 --> 10:00.642
All right.
This was special.

10:00.642 --> 10:02.185
Um, Zeke is my friend.

10:02.185 --> 10:03.853
Jared is my partner.

10:03.853 --> 10:06.815
"Partner"? Wow.

10:08.483 --> 10:10.151
Why don't you go back
to the apartment?

10:10.151 --> 10:12.570
Uh, you know, I got something
I gotta take care of.

10:12.570 --> 10:14.113
Pleasure to meet you.

10:18.076 --> 10:20.245
Are you serious
right now?

10:20.245 --> 10:22.914
You have a random stranger
staying in your apartment.

10:22.914 --> 10:25.250
Y-You gonna put up
Griffin next?

10:25.250 --> 10:27.836
Zeke and I have been
having the same calling
for about a week now.

10:27.836 --> 10:30.672
I have been led to him.
We're trying to figure out why.

10:30.672 --> 10:33.550
That is all this is.

10:33.550 --> 10:36.302
Jared, come on.
Please try and understand.

10:36.302 --> 10:38.680
[ Scoffs ]

10:38.680 --> 10:44.644
♪♪

10:44.644 --> 10:46.688
[ Monitor beeping ]

10:46.688 --> 10:52.819
♪♪

10:52.819 --> 10:56.406
[ Handcuff rattles ]

10:56.406 --> 11:00.118
Griffin. Can you hear me?
I'm Detective Stone.

11:00.118 --> 11:03.288
I was on site when you were
pulled out of the water.

11:03.288 --> 11:05.290
I'm --
I'm in the hospital?

11:05.290 --> 11:07.667
Yes.
But somehow you're fine.

11:09.711 --> 11:11.045
Do you remember
what happened before?

11:11.045 --> 11:12.672
You were talking
about an explosion.

11:12.672 --> 11:15.675
You saw something.

11:15.675 --> 11:18.136
Can you tell me
about that?

11:18.136 --> 11:20.221
That happened?

11:20.221 --> 11:22.390
The bombing happened?

11:22.390 --> 11:23.725
Bombing?

11:26.060 --> 11:27.395
We think that's
it's going to happen,

11:27.395 --> 11:29.439
but we think
that we can stop it.

11:29.439 --> 11:30.690
Griffin, look at me.

11:30.690 --> 11:32.984
You need to focus right now,
okay?

11:32.984 --> 11:34.736
Do you recognize me?

11:34.736 --> 11:37.071
I was on Flight 828.

11:37.071 --> 11:38.990
I was supposed to die on that
plane, but I came back.

11:38.990 --> 11:41.326
And ever since I have,
I have been hearing things

11:41.326 --> 11:43.703
and seeings things,
just like you did.

11:43.703 --> 11:45.163
We refer to them
as callings.

11:45.163 --> 11:47.415
You have -- You've just
had a calling.

11:49.417 --> 11:51.878
Was it day or night
in your vision?

11:51.878 --> 11:56.674
♪♪

11:56.674 --> 11:58.343
It was dark.

11:58.343 --> 11:59.928
Okay. Were you in a city?
Were there any landmarks?

11:59.928 --> 12:01.346
Anything that might
help us identify

12:01.346 --> 12:03.389
the location
of this bombing?

12:03.389 --> 12:05.600
I'm a little lost here.

12:05.600 --> 12:09.646
I get it, but there's not
a lot of time, okay?

12:09.646 --> 12:12.023
What did you call it?

12:12.023 --> 12:13.608
A calling.

12:15.902 --> 12:19.614
You've just had a vision
of the future.

12:19.614 --> 12:22.116
I don't understand.
How is that possible?

12:22.116 --> 12:27.038
♪♪

12:27.038 --> 12:29.582
Olive: Dad, I put Griffin
on my board.

12:29.582 --> 12:32.627
Do you think he's the wolf
that Cal drew?

12:32.627 --> 12:34.337
Ben: He might be.

12:34.337 --> 12:36.965
But the police have him now,
so don't worry, all right?

12:36.965 --> 12:38.967
Mom and Cal okay?
Yep.

12:38.967 --> 12:43.012
Cal's making a pretty cool
art project for school.

12:43.012 --> 12:45.598
Popsicle stick
Art the Dragon.

12:45.598 --> 12:48.059
[ Laughs ] Cool.
Here's Mom.

12:49.936 --> 12:51.688
Hey.

12:51.688 --> 12:53.606
So what do you think?

12:53.606 --> 12:55.817
Is Griffin just like you
and the other passengers?

12:55.817 --> 12:58.403
He might be.

12:58.403 --> 13:02.240
He had a calling.
Something about an explosion.

13:03.366 --> 13:05.159
Where?
We don't know.

13:05.159 --> 13:07.912
They sedated him, so we have
to wait for it to wear off.

13:07.912 --> 13:10.331
Okay.
Is there anything I can do?

13:10.331 --> 13:12.166
Nothing yet.

13:12.166 --> 13:13.751
I'll be home soon.

13:13.751 --> 13:14.836
I love you.

13:14.836 --> 13:17.130
I love you, too.
Ben?

13:17.130 --> 13:18.715
Yeah?

13:18.715 --> 13:22.010
I'm so glad
we're a family again.

13:22.010 --> 13:24.679
Me too.

13:24.679 --> 13:32.145
♪♪

13:32.145 --> 13:35.481
So all you passengers.
You've all been having visions?

13:35.481 --> 13:37.025
Michaela: Some of us.

13:37.025 --> 13:39.402
Sometimes it's a phrase
or a command.

13:39.402 --> 13:40.778
But whatever form
it does take,

13:40.778 --> 13:42.405
it's telling us
something important.

13:42.405 --> 13:45.241
Vital. And it has
to be followed. Always.

13:45.241 --> 13:48.870
And what you see or hear...
it always comes true?

13:48.870 --> 13:51.914
Yeah, pretty much.

13:51.914 --> 13:54.250
That's incredible.

13:54.250 --> 13:58.046
In this case, Griffin, it could
stop a bombing and save lives.

13:58.046 --> 14:00.131
Which is why you need
to tell me exactly

14:00.131 --> 14:02.633
what you saw,
every detail.

14:04.719 --> 14:08.097
So if I'm saying that a bomb's
gonna go off...

14:08.097 --> 14:09.724
if I'm the only one
who knows where...

14:09.724 --> 14:11.434
Do you know where,
Griffin?

14:11.434 --> 14:15.063
...then I'm the only one
who can save the day.

14:16.689 --> 14:18.149
Son-of-a-gun.

14:20.651 --> 14:22.278
Let's go.
On your feet.

14:22.278 --> 14:24.030
I'm in the middle
of an interrogation right now.

14:24.030 --> 14:25.656
Got to finish
in the box.

14:25.656 --> 14:28.201
He's got a green light
for transpo, so we transpo.

14:28.201 --> 14:30.787
I'm glad we talked,
Detective.

14:30.787 --> 14:34.999
I'll be honest,
I thought I was going crazy.

14:34.999 --> 14:37.335
But it's true.

14:37.335 --> 14:40.421
A lot of people
are about to tragically die.

14:40.421 --> 14:46.469
♪♪

14:46.469 --> 14:49.472
Griffin, you work with me,
it'll only help your cause.

14:49.472 --> 14:52.308
A double-homicide charge?
That's tough to beat.

14:52.308 --> 14:54.936
I don't think those charges
are gonna stick.

14:54.936 --> 14:58.606
Once the D.A. hears I know how
to stop a mass murder.

14:58.606 --> 15:01.859
And if this "calling"
really is what you say it is,

15:01.859 --> 15:04.362
I'll be sleeping
in my own bed tonight.

15:04.362 --> 15:08.199
Looks like I got myself
a get-out-of-jail-free card.

15:08.199 --> 15:13.287
♪♪

15:13.287 --> 15:18.376
♪♪

15:22.255 --> 15:26.259
♪♪

15:26.259 --> 15:29.929
[ Door opens, closes ]

15:29.929 --> 15:33.057
He claims there's gonna be
an attack tonight, in Midtown.

15:33.057 --> 15:34.684
That's all he said?
Midtown?

15:34.684 --> 15:37.186
[ Scoffs ] He'll provide
the precise location

15:37.186 --> 15:39.105
in return for full immunity
on the murders.

15:39.105 --> 15:40.648
Agent Dayton is FBI.

15:40.648 --> 15:42.400
We have
to take this seriously.

15:42.400 --> 15:45.153
His claims line up with an alert
that went out this morning.

15:45.153 --> 15:47.405
The NSA's been picking
up chatter about
a terrorist attack.

15:47.405 --> 15:48.698
We got that, too.

15:48.698 --> 15:50.158
I have to run this
up the chain.

15:50.158 --> 15:51.701
Talk to
the U.S. Attorney.

15:51.701 --> 15:53.452
Full immunity's no joke.

15:53.452 --> 15:55.121
If he says
anything more...

15:55.121 --> 15:57.456
Of course.

15:57.456 --> 15:59.000
Vasquez.

16:02.670 --> 16:05.423
Perp steals $75 million,
kills 2 guards,

16:05.423 --> 16:07.758
now claims to have information
on a terrorist threat?

16:07.758 --> 16:09.510
He does?
Yeah.

16:09.510 --> 16:10.761
I need you two
over at the bank.

16:10.761 --> 16:12.138
They've got an eyewitness.

16:12.138 --> 16:14.015
Take a photo array,
we need an I.D.

16:14.015 --> 16:16.475
I think Griffin
is credible.

16:16.475 --> 16:18.811
I think he might actually
know something.

16:18.811 --> 16:22.064
[ Quietly ] The same way
you know things sometimes?

16:22.064 --> 16:24.775
Yeah. Look, Captain, we can't
let this happen. This immunity.

16:24.775 --> 16:26.777
He's literally
gonna get away with murder.

16:26.777 --> 16:28.696
It's out of our hands.
The FBI and the U.S. Attorney --

16:28.696 --> 16:30.781
Look, let me talk to him
one-on-one, okay?

16:30.781 --> 16:33.910
Try and get under his skin.
Make a connection.

16:33.910 --> 16:35.536
Cap,
I'll handle the bank.

16:35.536 --> 16:37.038
If she really thinks
this guy's legit,

16:37.038 --> 16:38.915
then let's let her do
what she needs to do.

16:38.915 --> 16:44.378
♪♪

16:44.378 --> 16:46.756
[ Breathing heavily ]

16:46.756 --> 16:50.843
♪♪

16:50.843 --> 16:53.304
Hey, it's me.
I really screwed up.

16:53.304 --> 16:54.680
Why? What happened?

16:54.680 --> 16:56.265
I told Griffin
about the callings.

16:56.265 --> 16:58.017
And I assumed that he wouldn't
be receiving them

16:58.017 --> 17:00.102
unless he was gonna do
the right thing.

17:00.102 --> 17:01.520
But now he's gonna
exploit them.

17:01.520 --> 17:03.105
He's not gonna tell us
what he saw

17:03.105 --> 17:05.775
unless he gets to walk
on the murder charges.

17:05.775 --> 17:07.360
Oh, my God.

17:07.360 --> 17:10.613
Look, Mick, there's no way
you could've known that.

17:10.613 --> 17:12.865
We've been so focused
on following the callings,

17:12.865 --> 17:16.744
we never even contemplated
somebody abusing them.

17:16.744 --> 17:18.412
Yeah, surprise.

17:18.412 --> 17:20.498
And in the meantime, the media
is starting to ask questions.

17:20.498 --> 17:21.624
Ben?
Yeah?

17:21.624 --> 17:23.668
Come look at this.

17:23.668 --> 17:24.961
Reddit's on fire.

17:24.961 --> 17:26.921
Believers,
Cody's people...

17:26.921 --> 17:28.297
Everybody's linking it
to 828.

17:28.297 --> 17:30.633
[ Sighs ] Listen to this,
from Reddit --

17:30.633 --> 17:31.968
"And now
a violent criminal

17:31.968 --> 17:33.469
has joined the ranks
of the passengers.

17:33.469 --> 17:34.929
He's no different
than they are."

17:34.929 --> 17:36.889
Look, I could really
use your help right now.

17:36.889 --> 17:38.724
Name it.
I don't have time
to do research.

17:38.724 --> 17:41.143
The U.S. Attorney is gonna make
a deal with this guy any second,

17:41.143 --> 17:42.520
and then we'll be
out of time.

17:42.520 --> 17:44.313
Okay. You think his calling
has the kind

17:44.313 --> 17:46.148
of specific information
they need?

17:46.148 --> 17:48.109
Yeah. He saw an explosion --
and I think he saw where.

17:48.109 --> 17:50.820
Okay, what kind of research
do I need to do?

17:50.820 --> 17:52.446
I'm gonna send you Griffin's
police record.

17:52.446 --> 17:54.573
He's been in and out of jail
since he was 15 years old.

17:54.573 --> 17:56.075
But I-I need more
than his rap sheet.

17:56.075 --> 17:57.577
I need something
to work with.

17:57.577 --> 18:00.454
I need something human,
something personal.

18:00.454 --> 18:02.290
Right, something that'll
make him think twice

18:02.290 --> 18:03.874
about exploiting
the callings.

18:03.874 --> 18:05.626
All right. Got it.

18:05.626 --> 18:07.044
Ben.

18:08.796 --> 18:10.881
Great. Cody.

18:10.881 --> 18:14.302
Okay, this whole thing
has just been taken up a notch.

18:14.302 --> 18:18.139
James Griffin is the proof.
These people are dangerous.

18:18.139 --> 18:20.057
And don't forget Ben Stone,
okay,

18:20.057 --> 18:21.976
came to my place of business
and physically assaulted me.

18:21.976 --> 18:24.020
And now one of them's
a murderer?

18:24.020 --> 18:27.398
We need to take care of them
before they take care of us.

18:27.398 --> 18:29.025
You need to get
on your Twitter,

18:29.025 --> 18:30.693
get on your Facebook,
get on your Insta--

18:30.693 --> 18:33.988
All right. I got to move fast.
See what Griffin knows.

18:33.988 --> 18:37.033
If he gets free, it'll just
rile up people like Cody.

18:37.033 --> 18:38.492
Then they'll come
after all of us.

18:38.492 --> 18:40.244
And not just with bricks.

18:40.244 --> 18:42.038
Let us help you.

18:42.038 --> 18:43.331
It's just research
that you need, right?

18:43.331 --> 18:45.499
You have a whole team
right here.

18:45.499 --> 18:49.003
Grace, are you sure we want
to expose Olive to -- to this?

18:49.003 --> 18:51.922
Olive is already
exposed to this.

18:51.922 --> 18:55.426
And besides, who can work the
Internet better than a teenager?

18:55.426 --> 18:57.678
Fair point.

18:57.678 --> 18:59.013
All right. Let's do this.

18:59.013 --> 19:06.228
♪♪

19:06.228 --> 19:09.023
[ Door closes ]

19:09.023 --> 19:11.776
I had the thing again.
The calling.

19:11.776 --> 19:15.571
Oh, yeah. That's not
gonna leave you alone.

19:15.571 --> 19:17.198
I'm not gonna
talk about my deal --

19:17.198 --> 19:20.201
No, you played me.
Good work.

19:20.201 --> 19:23.120
Your natural instinct kicked in,
and you took advantage

19:23.120 --> 19:25.664
of somebody who was trying
to look out for you.

19:25.664 --> 19:27.750
Just gotta be me.

19:27.750 --> 19:30.211
Do you?
Can you be someone else?

19:30.211 --> 19:33.214
I mean, you just got
a second chance at life.

19:33.214 --> 19:34.882
You can be anyone
you want.

19:34.882 --> 19:38.135
Sure, Detective. Tell me
who I can grow up to be one day.

19:38.135 --> 19:40.429
[ Cellphone chimes ]

19:42.973 --> 19:46.560
♪♪

19:46.560 --> 19:49.063
You know,
I keep thinking...

19:49.063 --> 19:52.400
you never really
had a chance.

19:52.400 --> 19:56.237
No parents, so you went into
foster system at five years old.

19:56.237 --> 19:58.906
In and out of juvie
after that.

19:58.906 --> 20:03.953
First arrest -- 15,
first prison stint -- 19.

20:03.953 --> 20:05.413
There's nothing in here
about your parents.

20:05.413 --> 20:07.623
Did they die?

20:07.623 --> 20:09.458
Or were you taken
from them?

20:09.458 --> 20:12.837
I mean,
drugs and alcohol?

20:12.837 --> 20:15.673
Abuse?

20:15.673 --> 20:17.425
Am I close?

20:17.425 --> 20:19.635
Have you got my first kiss
in there, too?

20:19.635 --> 20:21.929
I mean, it's a pretty typical
situation, actually.

20:21.929 --> 20:24.598
No family to speak of, so you
fall into the wrong crowd.

20:24.598 --> 20:27.852
There's all kinds of families,
Detective.

20:27.852 --> 20:30.271
Mine was every bit as real
and strong as yours.

20:30.271 --> 20:36.944
♪♪

20:36.944 --> 20:39.113
Clear the hall.
Move.

20:39.113 --> 20:41.323
Head back up.

20:41.323 --> 20:42.992
Excuse us, please.

20:42.992 --> 20:48.706
♪♪

20:48.706 --> 20:52.126
[ Breathing heavily ]

20:52.126 --> 20:59.383
♪♪

20:59.383 --> 21:02.470
Well, here's something.
He was constantly on the move.

21:02.470 --> 21:04.638
Brooklyn, Long Island,
Queens.

21:04.638 --> 21:06.724
He must've been moving
from foster home to foster home.

21:06.724 --> 21:08.476
Huh.

21:08.476 --> 21:10.769
He had a brother.

21:10.769 --> 21:12.313
Look at this.

21:12.313 --> 21:14.148
I went to
the Wayback Machine.

21:14.148 --> 21:17.234
It's a site that archives old
websites that no longer exist.

21:17.234 --> 21:20.446
There was this thing called
Myspace, it's hilarious.

21:20.446 --> 21:22.239
Griffin had an account.
Look at this.

21:22.239 --> 21:24.366
Long conversations
with his "brother."

21:24.366 --> 21:25.826
Some guy named
Devon Carrick.

21:25.826 --> 21:27.661
Not his
biological brother.

21:27.661 --> 21:29.872
Must've been an older friend?
A mentor?

21:29.872 --> 21:31.957
Or a foster brother.

21:31.957 --> 21:33.751
And then right here --

21:33.751 --> 21:36.128
"Brothers forever.
Rest in peace."

21:36.128 --> 21:39.340
May 3, 2004.
Does it say how he died?

21:39.340 --> 21:40.799
No.

21:40.799 --> 21:43.010
But if he had someone
he loved pass away,

21:43.010 --> 21:45.095
that could be
the connection to Zeke.

21:45.095 --> 21:47.932
And what connects both of them
to Michaela.

21:47.932 --> 21:49.850
Evie.

21:49.850 --> 21:52.686
Michaela's still trying
to forgive herself.

21:52.686 --> 21:55.648
Here it is. Obituary.
Okay.

21:55.648 --> 21:58.025
"Always in our hearts."
Here we go.

21:58.025 --> 22:00.528
"Fatally wounded
at the Rochester
Correctional Facility."

22:00.528 --> 22:02.488
Survived by his "family,"
in quotes.

22:02.488 --> 22:04.532
James Griffin,
Angela Graham.

22:04.532 --> 22:06.534
Can you --
Already on it.

22:06.534 --> 22:08.452
I mean, there must be like
100 Angela Grahams.

22:08.452 --> 22:10.246
It's such a common name.

22:10.246 --> 22:12.873
Yeah, but only one
Angela Graham plus foster care.

22:12.873 --> 22:14.625
Look at this.
She has a LinkedIn page.

22:14.625 --> 22:16.710
All of her foster-care stuff
is on here.

22:16.710 --> 22:18.671
Stopped in 1999.

22:18.671 --> 22:21.423
Huh.
Wait.

22:21.423 --> 22:24.593
Griffin was in Newark
until '98.

22:24.593 --> 22:26.720
Now she's in Harlem.
She runs a food bank.

22:26.720 --> 22:28.514
She might know
something helpful.

22:28.514 --> 22:30.891
Something Mick could use to
break through Griffin's shell.

22:30.891 --> 22:32.434
Convince him not
to make this deal.

22:32.434 --> 22:33.769
I'm gonna go see her.

22:33.769 --> 22:34.979
She's more likely
to talk in person.

22:34.979 --> 22:36.981
Wait, it should be me.
Grace.

22:36.981 --> 22:38.899
She might recognize you,
and she'll have her guard up

22:38.899 --> 22:40.067
because of the news.

22:40.067 --> 22:41.527
We need to stay
under the radar.

22:41.527 --> 22:43.362
And besides, I'll be able
to connect with her.

22:43.362 --> 22:44.947
Mother to mother.

22:44.947 --> 22:47.366
I can't deny that.

22:47.366 --> 22:50.077
Okay. Do it.
I'll text Mick.

22:50.077 --> 22:53.831
♪♪

22:53.831 --> 22:55.749
Why don't you tell me
about Devon Carrick?

22:58.544 --> 23:01.422
Where did you
get that name?

23:01.422 --> 23:03.257
Was he in your family?

23:03.257 --> 23:04.842
I'm not talking
about this.

23:04.842 --> 23:05.884
I'm just trying
to figure out

23:05.884 --> 23:07.553
how we're all connected,
Griffin.

23:09.972 --> 23:12.057
Tell me about Devon.
Where is he now?

23:12.057 --> 23:14.435
I said I'm not
talking about it!

23:16.812 --> 23:23.736
♪♪

23:23.736 --> 23:30.659
♪♪

23:30.659 --> 23:33.078
[ Dog barking ]

23:33.078 --> 23:39.835
♪♪

23:39.835 --> 23:46.550
♪♪

23:46.550 --> 23:53.307
♪♪

23:53.307 --> 23:55.017
[ Siren chirps ]

23:55.017 --> 23:58.520
♪♪

23:58.520 --> 24:00.564
Sir,
let me see your hands.

24:00.564 --> 24:05.110
♪♪

24:05.110 --> 24:06.403
Come on down.

24:06.403 --> 24:11.283
♪♪

24:17.164 --> 24:19.708
[ Knock on door ]
Dr. Bahl?

24:19.708 --> 24:22.461
Hi. Uh, how can I help you,
Doctor...?

24:22.461 --> 24:23.712
Matthews.

24:23.712 --> 24:27.925
I was actually wondering if
I could do something for you.

24:27.925 --> 24:31.470
I saw you earlier,
in the hall.

24:31.470 --> 24:36.225
Oh, I-I'm fine.
I just had allergies.

24:36.225 --> 24:38.894
I-I know
I'm being intrusive,

24:38.894 --> 24:42.481
but what I saw
wasn't allergies.

24:42.481 --> 24:44.775
There's nothing wrong
with talking to somebody.

24:44.775 --> 24:46.360
I'm more than happy
to make a referral.

24:46.360 --> 24:49.530
I'm fine. Thank you.

24:49.530 --> 24:52.950
Okay. If you say so.

24:52.950 --> 24:54.201
Sorry to intrude.

24:54.201 --> 24:55.994
[ Quietly ]
No, it's fine.

24:55.994 --> 25:03.168
♪♪

25:03.168 --> 25:08.799
♪♪

25:08.799 --> 25:09.967
What's going on?

25:09.967 --> 25:11.343
Look what the cat
dragged in.

25:11.343 --> 25:13.095
Caught in an attempted
break-in.

25:13.095 --> 25:14.555
Residence in Forest Hills.
What?

25:14.555 --> 25:16.348
It's not like that, okay?
You got the wrong idea.

25:16.348 --> 25:17.891
Of course we do.
Excuse me.

25:17.891 --> 25:19.643
Do you mind if we...

25:19.643 --> 25:21.478
Sit.
Okay.

25:21.478 --> 25:24.773
♪♪

25:24.773 --> 25:26.191
No,
you can't book him.

25:26.191 --> 25:28.152
Michaela,
I know guys like Zeke, okay?

25:28.152 --> 25:30.028
I got my badge doing 18 months
of buys and busts.

25:30.028 --> 25:31.905
I can practically smell
the junkie on this guy.

25:31.905 --> 25:33.866
That is such a leap, Jay.
You don't know that.

25:33.866 --> 25:36.076
He's refusing
to identify himself.

25:36.076 --> 25:37.995
He won't even give us
his last name.

25:37.995 --> 25:40.372
[ Scoffs ] Come on, Michaela.
I'm trying to protect you.

25:40.372 --> 25:42.499
I know you are, Jared.
But this is not how you do it.

25:42.499 --> 25:45.127
Zeke was brought into my life
for a reason.

25:45.127 --> 25:47.421
Come on, Mick.
Listen to yourself.

25:47.421 --> 25:49.256
You don't think that
about Griffin.

25:49.256 --> 25:50.674
So you're just gonna sweat out
one criminal,

25:50.674 --> 25:51.967
while potentially giving
another one a free pass?

25:51.967 --> 25:55.137
Zeke
is not like Griffin.

25:55.137 --> 25:57.514
[ Exhales sharply ]

25:57.514 --> 25:59.183
Okay.

25:59.183 --> 26:02.478
I know you want to believe
that that's true. I do.

26:02.478 --> 26:05.522
But, Mick, these callings you're
having, they're blinding you.

26:05.522 --> 26:07.024
You know next to nothing
about this guy.
You know what?

26:07.024 --> 26:08.817
I don't -- I don't have time
for this, okay?

26:08.817 --> 26:11.236
Please, just whatever you do,
do not book him until I free up.

26:11.236 --> 26:15.991
♪♪

26:15.991 --> 26:18.243
Michaela, I can explain.
I can't deal with this
right now.

26:18.243 --> 26:20.704
Whatever the hell is going on,
please just explain it later.

26:20.704 --> 26:30.422
♪♪

26:30.422 --> 26:31.673
[ Door closes ]

26:31.673 --> 26:37.846
♪♪

26:37.846 --> 26:39.431
I know what
you're going through.

26:43.352 --> 26:45.562
I was responsible for the death
of my best friend.

26:45.562 --> 26:47.856
She was practically
my sister.

26:47.856 --> 26:49.775
What are you
talking about?

26:49.775 --> 26:51.985
Devon's file.
It's all right here.

26:55.489 --> 26:57.241
It was supposed
to be simple, right?

26:57.241 --> 27:02.371
You and Devon were gonna pop in,
grab some cash.

27:02.371 --> 27:04.039
What happened?

27:04.039 --> 27:05.707
You know what happened.

27:05.707 --> 27:08.627
You have the report.

27:08.627 --> 27:11.922
The victim
was another customer.

27:11.922 --> 27:13.340
Just some guy.

27:15.592 --> 27:17.970
Do you remember
what he was buying?

27:17.970 --> 27:20.472
Powdered doughnuts.

27:20.472 --> 27:23.642
So he turns around
and sees two men in ski masks

27:23.642 --> 27:25.227
walk into the store.

27:25.227 --> 27:28.105
Decides he's gonna be a hero,
whips out his gun.

27:28.105 --> 27:29.398
Two shots
right in the chest.

27:29.398 --> 27:30.649
I know
how the story ends.

27:30.649 --> 27:32.442
Right,
so Devon goes to jail.

27:32.442 --> 27:34.653
Murder one.
Because he's the shooter.

27:34.653 --> 27:37.614
And we know
he's the shooter because...

27:37.614 --> 27:41.285
that's what you
told the police.

27:41.285 --> 27:43.495
I guess my question
here is...

27:43.495 --> 27:45.956
is that what really happened,
Griffin?

27:45.956 --> 27:47.749
It says you cut a deal.

27:47.749 --> 27:49.793
The first perp to turn gets
to frame the narrative, so...

27:49.793 --> 27:52.212
I don't want
to do this anymore.
No, of course you don't.

27:52.212 --> 27:54.423
'Cause you sent Devon to prison,
and that's where he died.

27:54.423 --> 27:56.508
You were the shooter,
weren't you?
I'm done talking about this!

27:56.508 --> 27:59.887
And you've carried that shame
with you for 15 years.

27:59.887 --> 28:03.891
I know because I have carried
the same shame.

28:06.351 --> 28:08.770
Griffin,
we are all connected.

28:08.770 --> 28:12.024
That is why you came back,
I'm sure of it.

28:12.024 --> 28:14.985
You're not the only one.

28:14.985 --> 28:16.987
We have all been given a chance
to start over.

28:16.987 --> 28:18.739
This is yours.

28:18.739 --> 28:21.325
♪♪

28:21.325 --> 28:22.951
[ Door opens ]

28:22.951 --> 28:24.286
Detective?

28:24.286 --> 28:30.459
♪♪

28:30.459 --> 28:34.671
♪♪

28:34.671 --> 28:38.050
[ Police radio chatter ]

28:39.343 --> 28:40.761
The U.S. Attorney
signed off.

28:40.761 --> 28:42.304
W-We're making the deal?

28:42.304 --> 28:44.514
Our terrorist unit has
corroboration from an asset.

28:44.514 --> 28:47.267
Some event in Midtown,
they think within the
next couple hours.

28:47.267 --> 28:48.977
AUSA's on his way.

28:48.977 --> 28:50.437
So whatever you're doing,
you need to wrap it up.

28:50.437 --> 28:52.272
If he's still on his way,
then we have time.

28:52.272 --> 28:53.857
Look, I'm getting close,
Captain.

28:53.857 --> 28:55.692
Please, don't tell him
that we've taken the deal.

28:55.692 --> 28:58.028
Just let me keep pushing,
okay?

29:02.824 --> 29:03.951
Okay.

29:07.955 --> 29:09.873
[ Keyboard clacking ]

29:13.752 --> 29:15.504
[ Sighs ]

29:15.504 --> 29:18.715
Quick as you can, guys.
We have a lot of mouths to feed.

29:18.715 --> 29:21.301
E-Excuse me.
Angela Graham?

29:21.301 --> 29:24.179
Hi. My name is Grace Stone.
Do you have a minute?

29:24.179 --> 29:26.348
There's a donation box
inside.

29:26.348 --> 29:27.724
Oh, no.

29:27.724 --> 29:30.352
I need to talk to you
about James Griffin.

29:30.352 --> 29:31.812
You were
his foster mother?

29:31.812 --> 29:33.355
I told the Post,
I'm not --

29:33.355 --> 29:35.691
No, I'm not a reporter.

29:35.691 --> 29:37.025
I'm a little busy here.

29:37.025 --> 29:39.778
James Griffin is a threat
to my family.

29:39.778 --> 29:41.697
To my children.

29:41.697 --> 29:44.366
It's a long story, but I need
to know what I'm dealing with.

29:46.535 --> 29:48.203
We can talk over here.

29:49.997 --> 29:55.335
Truth is, James Griffin
was just awful.

29:55.335 --> 29:58.130
Griffin had one friend
in the world,

29:58.130 --> 29:59.881
and he lost him.

29:59.881 --> 30:02.384
Devon Carrick?

30:02.384 --> 30:05.053
Devon treated him
like his little brother.

30:05.053 --> 30:11.685
♪♪

30:11.685 --> 30:15.397
This was taken the summer
I took the kids canoeing.

30:15.397 --> 30:18.400
Griffin lied,
said he could swim.

30:18.400 --> 30:20.527
His canoe tipped over,
Devon dove in,

30:20.527 --> 30:22.696
and pulled him
right out.

30:22.696 --> 30:25.198
He saved his life.

30:25.198 --> 30:27.409
A month later,
they were both in juvie.

30:27.409 --> 30:28.660
Two years.

30:28.660 --> 30:31.621
They never
came back home again.

30:31.621 --> 30:35.876
I honestly thought Griffin
was long dead...

30:35.876 --> 30:38.336
until I saw the news.

30:38.336 --> 30:42.215
I know
it's inappropriate...

30:42.215 --> 30:46.678
but I'm not sure I want
Griffin to go free.

30:46.678 --> 30:50.140
Maybe not everyone
deserves to be saved.

30:50.140 --> 30:57.147
♪♪

30:57.147 --> 30:59.399
Saanvi?

30:59.399 --> 31:02.152
Hey.
What's going on?

31:06.698 --> 31:09.534
I just don't
feel like myself.

31:09.534 --> 31:12.454
I'm jumpy.
I keep having these episodes.

31:12.454 --> 31:14.915
And I know what it is,
intellectually --

31:14.915 --> 31:16.208
PTSD.

31:16.208 --> 31:17.709
The symptoms are classic,
I know that,

31:17.709 --> 31:19.294
and I know I should talk
to someone, and I will.

31:19.294 --> 31:22.714
Hey, hey.
It has only been one day.

31:22.714 --> 31:24.132
You know...

31:24.132 --> 31:26.676
don't be so hard
on yourself.

31:28.220 --> 31:31.306
You'll get through this,

31:31.306 --> 31:33.975
and in the meantime,
we're all here for you.

31:33.975 --> 31:35.393
Whatever you need.

31:40.857 --> 31:43.485
[ Exhales sharply ]

31:43.485 --> 31:46.571
Griffin's blood work,
it just came back.

31:46.571 --> 31:49.658
♪♪

31:49.658 --> 31:52.828
He's got the same
blood marker.

31:52.828 --> 31:56.498
Just like us,
just like Zeke.

31:56.498 --> 31:59.918
[ Sighs ]

31:59.918 --> 32:01.461
Damn.

32:04.172 --> 32:06.341
Well,
there's our proof.

32:06.341 --> 32:08.760
All this time,
I thought we were on the cusp

32:08.760 --> 32:11.680
of some earth-shattering
discovery about us that'll...

32:11.680 --> 32:14.558
I don't even know what.

32:14.558 --> 32:16.518
But that
it would be good.

32:19.020 --> 32:23.108
I don't think that
anymore.

32:23.108 --> 32:25.277
I can't help but think
that we're on verge

32:25.277 --> 32:27.404
of discovering
something awful.

32:27.404 --> 32:30.323
♪♪

32:30.323 --> 32:32.909
Griffin:
I didn't have a choice --
Or maybe you betrayed your friend to save yourself.

32:32.909 --> 32:34.703
You cut a deal,
you got away with murder,

32:34.703 --> 32:35.996
and Devon paid the price.

32:35.996 --> 32:37.581
We're done here.

32:37.581 --> 32:39.875
I don't give a damn
about Devon Carrick, never have.

32:39.875 --> 32:41.459
Talk to my lawyer.

32:41.459 --> 32:43.295
[ Cellphone chimes ]

32:43.295 --> 32:51.052
♪♪

32:51.052 --> 32:53.096
Seems to me like you
did care about Devon.

32:55.515 --> 32:57.726
How did you get that?

32:57.726 --> 33:01.188
Griffin, you made a deal
that ruined your life.

33:01.188 --> 33:02.939
You are about
to do it again.

33:02.939 --> 33:04.107
Tell me what you saw
in that calling.

33:04.107 --> 33:05.150
Tell me what
is going to happen.

33:05.150 --> 33:07.485
You did not come back from the
dead to get away with murder.

33:07.485 --> 33:09.154
That is not
what this is about.

33:09.154 --> 33:12.991
♪♪

33:12.991 --> 33:14.367
That's enough, Detective.

33:14.367 --> 33:16.411
You have the chance
to put this right.

33:16.411 --> 33:18.538
People's lives
are at stake.

33:18.538 --> 33:20.498
Please.

33:20.498 --> 33:22.167
Detective, let's go.

33:23.919 --> 33:26.171
It was nice chatting with you,
Detective.

33:26.171 --> 33:33.178
♪♪

33:33.178 --> 33:36.681
[ Wolf growling ]

33:36.681 --> 33:43.230
♪♪

33:46.900 --> 33:54.824
♪♪

33:54.824 --> 34:04.417
♪♪

34:04.417 --> 34:06.336
[ Door buzzes ]

34:06.336 --> 34:12.467
♪♪

34:12.467 --> 34:14.427
[ Door closes ]

34:16.137 --> 34:18.098
Thank you.

34:18.098 --> 34:20.892
Yeah, well, I'm ready
for that explanation now.

34:20.892 --> 34:24.104
You want to tell me why you
broke into that house?

34:24.104 --> 34:27.274
[ Inhales,
exhales deeply ]

34:27.274 --> 34:28.692
It's my mom's house.

34:30.610 --> 34:33.196
Oh.

34:33.196 --> 34:35.824
I mean, I'm glad
that you went to see her, but...

34:35.824 --> 34:37.909
most of the time
when people go see their mom,

34:37.909 --> 34:40.870
they just knock on the door
or ring the doorbell.

34:40.870 --> 34:42.747
I couldn't just show up.

34:42.747 --> 34:45.083
There's too much history.

34:45.083 --> 34:47.544
I wanted to make sure she's,
I don't know, in a good place,

34:47.544 --> 34:50.463
you know, t-that she's strong
enough to see me again.

34:50.463 --> 34:52.632
I thought
if I could get inside,

34:52.632 --> 34:55.051
maybe I could --
maybe I could tell.

34:55.051 --> 34:56.469
Zeke, she's your mother.

34:56.469 --> 34:58.388
I caused her
a lot of pain.

34:58.388 --> 35:01.600
I broke her heart.
More than once.

35:01.600 --> 35:04.311
Knocking on that door
is just gonna break her
heart all over again.

35:05.895 --> 35:08.898
I want to tell you everything,
and I will.

35:08.898 --> 35:12.193
One step at a time.

35:12.193 --> 35:15.196
I'm not like that guy
you've got holed up, Michaela.

35:15.196 --> 35:17.866
I need you
to believe in me.

35:17.866 --> 35:20.118
I-I-I think I came back here
for a reason, too.

35:20.118 --> 35:22.454
I-I'm just trying
to figure out what that is.

35:22.454 --> 35:28.084
♪♪

35:28.084 --> 35:30.003
[ Door buzzes ]

35:33.840 --> 35:35.050
Let's go.

35:35.050 --> 35:37.719
You're releasing me?

35:37.719 --> 35:39.429
What about your Boy Scout?
He's not gonna be happy.

35:39.429 --> 35:40.847
Yeah, damn right
he's not.

35:40.847 --> 35:42.849
So prove to me
that I made the right choice.

35:42.849 --> 35:45.060
Look, you came back
to make things better.

35:45.060 --> 35:48.396
So start with yourself.
Go see your mom.

35:48.396 --> 35:51.274
Come on.
Can you walk him out?

35:58.948 --> 36:00.367
You released him?

36:00.367 --> 36:02.869
[ Sighs ] He doesn't belong
in there, Jared.

36:02.869 --> 36:04.037
I trust him.

36:04.037 --> 36:05.872
Because
he had a calling?

36:05.872 --> 36:08.083
Mick, what if another person
comes back?

36:08.083 --> 36:09.376
And then another?
And another?

36:09.376 --> 36:11.753
Are you just gonna
trust them all?

36:11.753 --> 36:14.422
I don't think that's what
you're really upset about.

36:14.422 --> 36:18.134
Look, you have every reason,
but...

36:18.134 --> 36:21.096
Come on.
Leave Zeke out of it.

36:21.096 --> 36:29.396
♪♪

36:29.396 --> 36:36.403
♪♪

36:36.403 --> 36:38.655
[ Cellphone chimes ]

36:42.784 --> 36:44.661
What is it?

36:44.661 --> 36:47.914
Griffin just used a calling to
literally get away with murder.

36:47.914 --> 36:50.583
[ Sighs ]

36:50.583 --> 36:53.294
What more could we have done
to reach him?

36:53.294 --> 36:55.422
Maybe he couldn't
be reached.

36:58.341 --> 37:01.886
Grace,
what if we're wrong?

37:01.886 --> 37:04.347
About what?

37:04.347 --> 37:09.686
Everything --
Zeke, the callings...

37:09.686 --> 37:11.813
Everything I've been doing
is based on the notion

37:11.813 --> 37:16.568
that there is some kind
of benevolent power behind them.

37:16.568 --> 37:19.487
But what if there isn't?
What then?

37:22.115 --> 37:24.159
What are we a part of?

37:27.996 --> 37:31.749
What if it's not about
the callings themselves?

37:31.749 --> 37:35.920
What if it's about how people
choose to use them?

37:38.423 --> 37:39.757
The wolf.

37:39.757 --> 37:43.678
♪♪

37:43.678 --> 37:45.263
Griffin.

37:45.263 --> 37:49.100
Once a predator,
always a predator.

37:49.100 --> 37:51.686
But then, why --
why would a calling

37:51.686 --> 37:53.563
be given
to someone like that?

37:53.563 --> 37:57.984
Someone irredeemable?

37:57.984 --> 37:59.986
To show us we can use
the calling for evil

37:59.986 --> 38:02.947
just as easily
as we can for good.

38:02.947 --> 38:06.075
And get away with it?

38:06.075 --> 38:10.997
♪♪

38:10.997 --> 38:18.838
♪♪

38:18.838 --> 38:21.007
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

38:21.007 --> 38:29.307
♪♪

38:29.307 --> 38:39.317
♪♪

38:39.317 --> 38:41.277
[ Doorbell buzzes ]

38:41.277 --> 38:49.953
♪♪

38:49.953 --> 38:58.628
♪♪

38:58.628 --> 39:07.262
♪♪

39:07.262 --> 39:15.979
♪♪

39:21.484 --> 39:23.319
Oh, good.

39:23.319 --> 39:27.282
I was worried I wouldn't
get a chance to say goodbye.

39:27.282 --> 39:29.075
Griffin,
I've seen what happens

39:29.075 --> 39:34.330
when the callings are exploited,
or abused.

39:34.330 --> 39:37.000
Detective...

39:37.000 --> 39:40.044
your thinking
has been far too narrow.

39:40.044 --> 39:43.590
These callings are capable
of so much more.

39:43.590 --> 39:46.634
I'm gonna take them
to a whole new level.

39:46.634 --> 39:53.099
♪♪

39:53.099 --> 39:55.476
Mr. Griffin,
you're a very lucky man.

39:55.476 --> 39:58.980
Assuming your information
bears out, we have a deal.

39:58.980 --> 40:02.525
So tell us,
where's the bomb hidden?

40:02.525 --> 40:10.908
♪♪

40:10.908 --> 40:13.494
I hope you don't get yourself
in a twist.

40:13.494 --> 40:16.122
♪♪

40:16.122 --> 40:19.250
[ Indistinct conversations ]

40:19.250 --> 40:24.964
♪♪

40:24.964 --> 40:30.720
♪♪

40:30.720 --> 40:33.264
[ Siren chirps ]

40:33.264 --> 40:36.768
Everybody, move back!

40:36.768 --> 40:40.813
[ Indistinct shouting ]

40:40.813 --> 40:47.987
♪♪

40:47.987 --> 40:55.203
♪♪

40:55.203 --> 41:02.377
♪♪

41:02.377 --> 41:04.253
[ Beeping ]

41:06.506 --> 41:14.055
♪♪

41:14.055 --> 41:21.562
♪♪

41:21.562 --> 41:22.605
[ Beeping stops ]

41:27.443 --> 41:30.488
Clear. We're clear.

41:30.488 --> 41:32.657
[ Wolf growling ]

41:32.657 --> 41:42.208
♪♪

41:42.208 --> 41:44.252
[ Growling continues ]

41:44.252 --> 41:49.757
♪♪

41:49.757 --> 41:51.300
Hey.

41:52.760 --> 41:54.387
Hey, you okay?

41:56.222 --> 41:58.474
Mick, they diffused the bomb.
We're good.

41:58.474 --> 42:00.560
No. We're not.

42:00.560 --> 42:02.812
[ Growling continues ]

42:02.812 --> 42:07.108
♪♪

42:10.987 --> 42:18.786
♪♪

42:18.786 --> 42:26.586
♪♪

42:26.586 --> 42:34.427
♪♪

42:34.427 --> 42:42.226
♪♪
